<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="hot-adj">hot <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /hɒt/    美 /hɑːt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>热的；烫的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 cold </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's very hot for May.
五月份这样的天算很热了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The bar serves hot and cold drinks.
那家酒吧供应冷热饮。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Eating food that's too hot may cause cancer.
吃太烫的食物可能会导致癌症。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>辣的</strong></h4>
<p>反 mild </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Shanghai food, a little bit sweet, differs from Sichuan food that is rather hot.
沪菜，稍微有点甜，与很辣的川菜不一样。</p><footer>2009 重庆</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>急躁的；激烈的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>hot temper</strong> / a hot fight
急脾气/激战</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a hot issue / topic
热门话题</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>[非正式用语] 流行的；最新的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>hot sellers / hot news
畅销品/最新消息</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-hot-on">be hot on</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[非正式用语] 迷恋；喜爱：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In fact, Hollywood has been hot on live animals lately.
事实上，近来好莱坞对活体动物很感兴趣。</p><footer>2020全国</footer></div></div>